description.narrative: UNICEF worked in 7 of 22 regions through classroom construction, catch up classes and support to children with disabilities. 47,042 children from preprimary to lower secondary attended catch-up classes and received pedagogical materials. 12,123 households benefitted from cash transfers to school their children. For future programming, a mechanism to help children in catch-up classes to return to the regular system needs to be developed. This will benefit the most vulnerable children, such as those with disabilities. This will require inter-sectoral efforts from education, child protection, C4D, social policy and health. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:31/12/2019
